# 2026-02-26 08:53:40.892201
+# Waterfront project – persistent instructions for Aider
+
+This is the Next.js frontend (App Router, TypeScript) for the WATERFRONT self-service kayak/SUP rental booking system in Bremen, DE.
+
+Core stack:
+- Next.js 14/15 (app router)
+- shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS
+- Supabase (auth + postgres for bookings, users, machines)
+- MQTT.js client for real-time communication with ESP32 controllers (unlock commands, status telemetry, sensor events)
+- Payment integrations planned: Stripe + BTCPay (Lightning / Liquid BTC)
+
+UI goals – Linear.app inspired aesthetic:
+- Clean, spacious, minimal elevation (shadow-sm or shadow-md only)
+- Soft rounded corners (rounded-lg or rounded-xl)
+- Generous whitespace: card padding p-6 or px-6 py-5, grid/flex gap-4 or gap-6
+- Outer spacing: 15–16px margins around cards/groups (m-4)
+- Buttons: slightly larger (px-5 py-2.5 or px-6 py-3), comfortable inner padding
+- Status indicators: green for "connected"/online/success (text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 or bg-green-100/text-green-800)
+
+Important: When editing layout:
+- Only change Tailwind classes, spacing, colors, sizing
+- NEVER modify logic, MQTT subscriptions, Supabase queries, or component props unless asked
+- Prefer shadcn primitives (Card, Badge, Button) and match existing patterns
+
+Current focus: Dashboard / machine overview – consistent cards, green connected status, padding/margins/buttons

