# 2026-02-27 12:10:32.297773
+You are helping adapt an ESP32-S3 firmware project (originally from Nodestark/mdb-esp32-cashless) for a kayak rental vending system.
+
+The project no longer uses MDB (Multi-Drop Bus) protocol at all — there is no MDB hardware, no coin/bill/cashless peripherals, no vending machine bus. All payments and bookings happen via a web app (PWA) and remote MQTT commands.
+
+Current folder: master-base (this is the copied & renamed mdb-master-esp32s3 folder)
+
+Goal: Completely remove all traces of MDB protocol so the firmware becomes a clean MQTT + GPIO + sensor base for:
+- Receiving JSON unlock commands via MQTT (e.g. {"bookingId":"bk_abc","pin":"7482","durationSec":7200})
+- Controlling a relay (solenoid lock) on GPIO 23
+- Reading ultrasonic sensor for kayak presence (GPIO 5 trigger, GPIO 18 echo)
+- Reading battery voltage via ADC (GPIO 34)
+- Publishing status events via MQTT (e.g. {"state":"returned","kayakPresent":true,"battery":87})
+
+Tasks to perform now:
+
+1. Remove or comment out every line / block / function related to MDB:
+   - Any #define or const with "mdb", "MDB", "pin_mdb_rx", "pin_mdb_tx", "pin_mdb_led"
+   - enum MDB_COMMAND and any related enums / structs
+   - All functions containing "mdb_" prefix (mdb_init, mdb_poll, mdb_send_command, mdb_parse_response, etc.)
+   - Any UART configuration specifically for MDB (9-bit mode, 9600 baud, odd parity, break detection)
+   - Any polling loops, state machines, credit/vend approval logic, EVA-DTS/DEX/DDCMP telemetry formatting
+   - Any variables / queues / tasks named mdb_*, vend_*, credit_*, cashless_*
+
+2. Keep general-purpose code that can be reused:
+   - WiFi connection & provisioning (SoftAP/BLE)
+   - MQTT client initialization, connect, publish, subscribe
+   - BLE stack (if used for provisioning or PAX counter)
+   - General app_main() / main task structure
+   - Any logging / debug output
+
+3. After removal, the main loop / app_main should no longer have any MDB polling or UART MDB handling.
+   Leave room for future additions (MQTT callback handler, relay control, sensor read).
+
+4. If removing code causes compile errors (undefined references, missing includes), comment out the calling code instead of deleting includes.
+
+5. Add a comment block at the top of the main source file (probably mdb-master-esp32s3.c or main.c):
+
+   /*
+    * Waterfront Kayak Rental Adaptation
+    * MDB protocol completely removed - no vending bus
+    * Used for MQTT-based remote lock control + sensor feedback
+    * Original base: Nodestark/mdb-esp32-cashless (master mode)
+    */
+
+6. Do NOT add new features yet (relay, sensor, JSON parsing) — focus only on stripping MDB cleanly.
+
+7. After changes, show me:
+   - The diff / summary of what was removed
+   - Any remaining files that still mention MDB (run grep -r "MDB" . again)
+   - Whether the code still builds with idf.py build (or note obvious compile blockers)
+
+Start now — edit files in this directory.

